div.p:
1. If you build Gods house, God will build Houses for you, as he did for the Hebrew Midwives, he will blesse and prosper you.Ex. 1.21. Remember what the Prophet Haggai saith. Is it time for you, O yee, to dwell in your ceiled houses, and this house lye waste? Now therefore, thus saith the Lord;
               Hagg. 1.4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9.
               consider your wayes, Yee have sown much, and bring in little, yee eat, but ye have not enough, ye cloath you, but there is none warm; and he that earneth wages, earneth wages to put it into a bag with holes. Thus saith the Lord, Consider your wayes, go up to the Mountain, and bring Wood and build the house, and I will take pleasure in it, and I will be glorified, saith the Lord, &c. Read also, Verse 9, 10, 11.
